CHICAGO-The white Canadian
common in law wife of a Negro
policy king, Mrs. Rose Kennedy,
90, has conferred with an attor-
ney. She hopes to recover most
of the $763,233 found in the
apartment after Lawrence Wake
field, 80 died.


Mrs. Kennedy said she came
to Chicago 81 years ago when
her previous husband began to
operate two policy wheels. Wake
field worked for the couple and
moved in after her husband died.

He poses with the Ed Sanders
Memorial Trophy awarded for the
outstanding poxing performance
of the tournament.


Earnest is winner of the out
standing civilian boxing award
and also holds a similar award
as member of the veterans
association.

Little Kimberly Heard, daugh-
ter of Mr.. and Mrs. Bobby Heard,
